reviewText: If Jesus and Marlon Brando had a baby, that baby would be 'Irish Car Bomb'. It is a masterfully crafted sequel to 'The White Russian', starring America's finest actor (Kurt Broz). The up-and-comer Jake McGee flexes some real acting muscles, including running with a chainsaw. I laughed, I cried, I understood what it meant to be alive. Please, do the universe a favor and get this film.
